&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ardent&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Cybersecurity Analytics Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our team.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is&amp;nbsp;an on-site position in Lanham, MD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Description:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ardent is seeking a Cybersecurity Analytics Lead to support the IRS Cybersecurity Fraud Analytics and Monitoring (CFAM) program through fraud analytics operations, predictive analysis, forensic investigations, and cybersecurity monitoring activities. This role will support large-scale analytics initiatives focused on detecting anomalous, malicious, and fraudulent activity across IRS online application ecosystems.&lt;/p&gt;
